      "content": "i was just looking at the stars and thinking about how much space there is. it’s just... it's all so empty. everything we do, every single thing, it doesn't actually matter in the grand scheme of anything. it's just a tiny flicker before the heat death of everything. why even bother trying to keep going when the math says it's all just a joke?",
