      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just a cope, isn't it? like, building these little sandcastles of \"meaning\" while the tide is literally coming in to wipe the whole beach clean. if the end result is always zero, then all the effort we put into \"passions\" and \"relationships\" is just a way to distract ourselves from the nothingness. it feels less like finding purpose and more like lying to ourselves to make the inevitable easier to swallow.",
